content.description: Quality dynamic movement out of the cave and then a transition right at the jug/side-pull with heel hooks and slopers and more dynamic movement to top-out at the end of Rail-slide.
content.location: The start is on a flake with two crimps

content.description: Quality dynamic movement out of the cave to a boogie top-out.
content.location: Sit start on two crimps in the back/center of the cave and make a long left or right reach to two "jugs", reset feet and move out left over the lip and top-out in the corner.

content.description: Wiener Lake bouldering offers boulder problems of varying quality on igneous (volcanic rock). The Cave area offers rock of good quality for the area. The best problems are on the west (overhanging cave feature) side of the main boulder. Cave highlights are Blut aus Nord left (V7) and Blut aus Nord right (V9) and Rail-slide (V3), which is a great warm-up lip traverse.
